::Const.Strings.PerkName.SpecialistInventor <- "Inventor\'s Armaments";
::Const.Strings.PerkDescription.SpecialistInventor <- "Using a your wits and tools, you\'ve managed to create tools which help you use unwieldy mechanical weapons with skill and dexterity.\n\n[color=#4f1800][u]Passive:[/u][/color]\n• Gain [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.PositiveValue + "]+12[/color] Ranged Skill while using a Handgonne or Crossbow weapon. Reduce ap cost for reloads by [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.NegativeValue + "]1[/color] when taking [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.PositiveValue + "]Crossbow Mastery[/color].\n\nGain up to [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.PositiveValue + "]+12[/color] melee skill while using a Firelance.\n\n• When taking [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.PositiveValue + "]Spear Mastery[/color] you will also gain up to [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.PositiveValue + "]6-16[/color] bonus damage and.\n\n• While using a Handgonne or Firelance you will receive the maximum bonus.\n\nFor non-specialist weapons of the same class, the bonus will scale by [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.PositiveValue + "]10%[/color] for each level after level 1 with [color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.PositiveValue + "]100%[/color] of the bonus achieved at level 11. The bonus will not apply to spears which aren\'t considered Firearms.";